  "text": "Because of the importance of accurate protein folding sophisticated cellular mechanisms have evolved to ensure correct protein folding and efficient disposal of irreversibly misfolded proteins. These mechanisms are designed to ensure that only properly folded proteins can exit from the ER. Proteins enter the ER in an unfolded state via a heterotrimeric Sec61p channel. Various chaperones residing in the ER facilitate folding of these nascent polypeptides via modifications such as disulphide bind formation and N-linked glycosylation. Faulty polypeptides generated via this process are disposed of [CITATION_1] .",
